【24 Hours Surveillance】- Makes the parking monitor of your dashcam work! Keeps it powered even after the engine is off, protect your car all the time! The vehicle hard-wire kit connected to a car battery or fuse box power can uninterruptedly supply power for the dash camera for 24 hours. It can even supply power when the car is turned off.

【Wide Compatibility】- Input: 12V-24V; Output:5V/2A(also fits for 1A) this hardwire kit is compatible with all car mini USB dashcam such as dashcam, mirror cam, GPS navigator, accepts voltage from any type of vehicle runs on 12-24V. Please Note the Smart hardwire kit NOT Compatible with Pruveeo J20-4CH/J40 mirror dash cam.

【Smart Display Screen】- Digital smart display screen to show the current voltage and the corresponding current to 5V voltage. Control the current value of car at any time, understand more about car usage. The Best Choice of Your Beloved Car.

【What Will You Get】- You will get 1 x upgraded the 3rd generation dashcam Mini USB Hardwire Kit,1 x installing crowbar, 8 x fuse tap cable, 4 x Cable Hiding Clips dash cam hardwire with the most popular fuse types will meet the applications for most car models.

Installation Steps: 1.Find ACC position Open the fuse box to find out the correct fuse slot. If you need to find an ignition switched fuse to keep 24H constant power supply, then turn off the car and remove the key to see which fuse slots stays lit on. 2.Connect the Yellow Wire(BATT / B +) Connect this yellow wire to the constant power fuse in the fuse box of your car. Gently remove the fuse you identified. Install the fuse you just removed into the installation kit add-a-fuse circuit. Plug the add-a-circuit into the fuse box in the correct orientation. 3.Connect the Red Wire(ACC) Once you've determined which fuse slots you need to use you can crimp the red wire of your hard wire kit onto the Add-A-Fuse. Gently remove the fuse you identified. Install the fuse you just removed into the installation kit add-a-fuse circuit. Plug the add-a-circuit into the fuse box in the correct orientation. 4.Connect the Black Wire(GND) This black wire (which is in the shape of a C) is connected to the metal parts of the vehicle. There are screw nails and metal parts near the fuse boxes in many cars. Connect the black wire to the any metal bolt in the car.To attach the grounding terminal, loosen the nut or bolt enough to slip it in and tighten it back up afterwards.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Limited Compatibility and Functionality - A Disappointing Experience
reviews.reviewText: Rating: ★☆☆☆☆I purchased the Pruveeo Dash Cam Hardwire Kit with the expectation that it would keep my dash cam running even when my vehicle, a 2004-2008 Ford F150, was completely off. Unfortunately, my experience with this product was far from satisfactory, leading me to a 1-star rating.Issues Encountered: 1. Compatibility: The first major issue was compatibility. The kit is designed for specific types of fuse boxes, and unfortunately, mine was not one of them. The presence of multiple relays around the desired fuses in my fuse box rendered the provided tools useless. This was a significant oversight, as there was no disclaimer or warning about potential incompatibility with vehicles like mine. 2. Installation: What was supposed to be a DIY project turned into a need for professional installation. Despite this added expense and effort, the technician informed me that the kit did not work as intended. The dash cam would turn off along with the vehicle, defeating the purpose of the hardwire kit.Positive Aspects:Despite the issues, the concept of the kit is promising. If it were to work as advertised, it would indeed be an amazing addition to any compatible vehicle, providing continuous dash cam operation without draining the car battery.Product Quality:The kit’s overall quality also left much to be desired. The sticky tabs meant to secure the wires were not only inadequate in number but also lacked the necessary adhesiveness, further complicating the installation process.Suggestions for Improvement: • Universal Compatibility: It’s crucial for the kit to include a wider range of tools and connectors to ensure compatibility with all types of fuse boxes, especially those in common vehicles like the Ford F150. • Quality of Accessories: Enhancing the quality of the sticky tabs would greatly improve the user experience, ensuring secure and discreet wire placement.Final Thoughts:I can only recommend the Pruveeo Dash Cam Hardwire Kit to individuals who are certain of their vehicle’s compatibility with the kit. The lack of clear compatibility information and the poor quality of installation accessories significantly undermine the product’s value. Potential buyers should proceed with caution and perhaps look for alternatives that offer greater flexibility and reliability.
